column2: Sunny- 62 F- ice on 11/20/89- ice off 4/12
Sunny- 60 F- light clouds- breeze- .2" rain since 5/13
Sunny- 61 F- lt. breeze- .6" rain since last report
Lt. clouds- overcast to n- 70 F- breezy- trace of rain since last report
Partly cloudy- winds gusty- 67 F- 1.1" rain since last report
Few clouds to n- 75 F- 6" rain since last report
Partly sunny- windy- 60 F- .7" rain since last report
Sunny- 73 F- suspended algae- .6" rain since last reading
Intermittent sun- 74 F- lt. breeze- 2.2" rain since last reading.
Beautiful- 73 F- no rain since last report
Thick weeds around edge last few weeks.- sunny- clear- 73 F- white particulate in lake- .4" rain since last report
Weeds- slight. overcast- 78 F- 2" rain since last report- heavy particulate under surf.- worst this year
Variable sun/clouds- 78 F- mild breeze- .7" rain since last report
Sunny- foggy in a.m.- 71 F- 1.65" rain 8/9- much algae particulate/heavy weeds
Clear- sunny- 74 F- 2.2" rain since last report
Sunny- 77 F- much algae/floating weeds- aquatic plants turning brown
Overcast- 68 F- much algae- 3.2" rain since last report- lake highest this year
Sunny- beautiful- 78 F- .7" rain since last reading- heavy algae/weeds- lake continues rising
Sunny/cloudy- 63 F- 1.3" rain since last reading- lake near all time high
Slight. breeze- mostly sunny- 70 F- .3" rain since last report- weeds dying
Obvious deterioration of water clarity within past week.  Asumption is that the lake water turned over- thereby uprooting excessive amounts of Northern Millfoil which are adrift throughout the lake.
Overcast.  Due to lateness of ice off- and my schedule- this first report is a bit past the two week from ice off time limit.
Sunny Day.  Water temps higher than same time last year by 8 degrees.  Also water clarity is the worst I have seen in a few years.  Shore lines littered with globs of decayed matter.
Somewhat sunny day- but very windy.  Water unusally murkey but feel it might be due to the unusually wet summer.

column1: Water levels remain normal to a bit high for August.  Weeds- although no signs of any AIS- seem to be heavy this year.  Purple Loosestrife still continues to be apparent in the channel between Gunlock and Shishebogama- but is being monitored and controled by our Lake Association volunteers.

column2: Partly cloudy- breezy.  Water quality looks better than a month ago.
Sunny- calm.  Very high water levels.  Highest I have seen in a number of years- for this time of year.

column1: Over 9" more water in lake today- than mid June.

column2: Water levels remain high.  Shore lands are saturated with water- and soggy.  Rains continue.
Sunny Breezy Day.  Water levels remain at the high end of normal range.  Lake water remains at early spring levels. High Water levels and rain continues.
